# Project skill categories (BR-028)

When editing **`projects/*/config.json`** `skills` or scripts that set `skills`:

## Allowed IDs only

`skills` must be an array of **one or more** of these strings (or `[]` if none apply yet):

| ID | Site label |
|----|------------|
| `plush` | Plush |
| `electronic` | Electronic |
| `mechanical` | Mechanical |
| `paintjob` | Paint |

**Not allowed** in JSON: `sewing`, `cleaning`, `electronics`, `restuffing`, `figure repair`, `gluing`, etc.

## Before saving

- Run or apply: `node scripts/normalize-project-skills.mjs` (or `normalizeSkills()` from [`scripts/lib/normalize-skills.mjs`](../../scripts/lib/normalize-skills.mjs)).
- Full reference: [`docs/project-skills.md`](../../docs/project-skills.md).

## Mapping (quick)

- Fabric / plush / restuff / clean → **`plush`**
- Wiring / battery / sound / solder → **`electronic`**
- Gears / motors / wind-up / mechanical assembly → **`mechanical`**
- Figure glue, resin, paint, finish → **`paintjob`**

If you change the canonical list, update **`normalize-skills.mjs`**, **`new/js/skills.js`**, and **`docs/project-skills.md`** together.
